&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/terms/uses/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/terms/uses/> ;
  schema:name "Uses" ;
  schema:description "Use is a relation O uses R — operation O uses resource R — asserting that O requires R as a necessary ingredient for its correct functioning: O cannot supply its own function correctly unless R supplies its function correctly. The defining structure: use is necessary dependency — not mere reference or documentation, but active reliance. Use is the coarsest of the operation-resource relations: reads, writes, consumes, takes, and produces are all refinements of uses that specify the access mode. The core formal content is Parnas's USES relation (1979): A USES B iff the correct functioning of A depends on the correct functioning of B." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:isPartOf &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/> ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/terms/uses/> ;
  rdfs:seeAlso "Reads, Writes, Consumes, Takes, Produces, Emits, Returns, Dependency, ComponentRelation" ;
  schema:identifier &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/tech/terms/uses/> .

